-dual-disc-brakes-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-1068x711.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-631x420.jpg 631w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-1068x711.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25125021/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-blade-fork-dual-disc-brakes-631x420.jpg 631w\"></a>Both fork lowers get a brake mount, allowing the Eidolon to run not one but two hydraulic disc brakes with 203mm rotors.</p><p>While the Ryuger Eidolon sure is interesting to gawp at, the brand say the coolest thing about it is the way in which the carbon frame is made. “<em>Whereas conventional carbon construction includes bladder bags and pre-formers to expand the carbon frame, Ryuger has developed a unique process eliminating the bags, using less carbon while increasing strength and agility on the road</em>” – Ryuger. No more detail than that, sorry.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension.jpg\" alt=\"ryuger eidolon carbon ebike commuter full suspension\" width=\"1200\" height=\"839\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-297x208.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-800x559.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-120x84.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-768x537.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-696x487.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-1068x747.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-601x420.jpg 601w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-100x70.jpg 100w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-297x208.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-800x559.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-120x84.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-768x537.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-696x487.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-1068x747.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-601x420.jpg 601w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131707/ryuger-eidolon-carbon-ebike-full-suspension-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>While this ebike is designed around a 29″ wheelset, it can also take 27.5″ or 26″ wheels with wider rims to fit chunkier tires more suited to riding off-road. No specific tire clearance claims are made, though it does come spec’d with 2.5″ Maxxis Hookworm tires.</p><h3>What about the motor?</h3><p>Of course, there’s so much going on here that you might well forget the Ryuger Eidolon is in fact a commuter ebike. It runs a Shimano Steps E8000 motor with a Shimano 504Wh downtube-integrated battery.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike.jpg\" alt=\"ryuger eidolon avocado frame carbon full suspension commuter ebike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"778\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-297x193.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-800x519.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-120x78.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-768x498.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-696x451.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-1068x692.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-648x420.jpg 648w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-297x193.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-800x519.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-120x78.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-768x498.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-696x451.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-1068x692.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/25131137/ryuger-eidolon-avocado-full-suspension-commuter-ebike-648x420.jpg 648w\"></a></p><h3>Ryuger Eidolon Full Suspension Commuter eBike Specs</h3><p>Seat Post: Ryuger Carbon Aero Adjustable</p><p>Cable Routing: Internal Cable&nbsp;</p><p>Front Forks: Ryuger Monocoque Carbon Girder 29″ Cane Creek DB Coil 190/50 400LBS</p><p>Rear Shock: Cane Creek DB Coil 190/50 650 LBS</p><p>Front and Rear Tires: Maxxis Hookworm 29″ x 2.5″</p><p>Battery: Shimano BT-E8035 504Wh Integrated&nbsp;</p><p>Display: Shimano SC-E6100</p><p>Motor Shimano: Steps E8000</p><p>Crankset Shimano Steps: FC-E8000</p><p>Rims: Ryuger Carbon 5 spoke 29″</p><p>Saddle: Prologo T Gale TT CPC Rail Nack Carbon with U Cage</p><p>Handle Bars: Ryuger Carbon Drop aero bars</p><p>Rear Derailleur: Shimano Di2 XT</p><p>Brakes: Front Tektro Twin system, Rear Shimano XT&nbsp;</p><p>Brake Levers: Shimano XT&nbsp;</p><p>Discs: Shimano Front Rotors 203mm x 2 /Rear 1 x 203mm&nbsp;</p><p>Stem: Ryuger</p><p>Pedals: Shimano XTR&nbsp;</p><p>Chainring: Digirit Carbon 48T&nbsp;</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>We don’t have any pricing information for the Ryuger Eidolon BR-RTS just yet but, we can tell you it will be available in Acid Avocado and Spacing Racing colorways.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ryugerbikes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Ryuger.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"00e62f5c3b5da0af8186508c5595ee8e6091695f8e0328139434d06708e554b5","category":"Cycling"}